{"id":192,"parent_id":190,"book_id":9398,"content_id":1,"language_id":1,"display_order":192,"title":"Revelation 2-3: Counsel for Seven Branches of the Church","subtitle":"","short_title":"Revelation 2-3: Counsel for Seven Branches of the Church","uri":"/manual/new-testament-student-study-guide/the-revelation-of-saint-john-the-divine/revelation-2-3-counsel-for-seven-branches-of-the-church","content":[["div",{"id":"container","role":"main"},["div",{"type":"chapter","uri":"/manual/new-testament-student-study-guide/the-revelation-of-saint-john-the-divine/revelation-2-3-counsel-for-seven-branches-of-the-church"},[".heading",{"id":"head3","uri":"/manual/new-testament-student-study-guide/the-revelation-of-saint-john-the-divine/revelation-2-3-counsel-for-seven-branches-of-the-church.head3"},["h1","Revelation 2–3"],[".subtitle","Counsel for Seven Branches of the Church"],[".",{"id":"f5","uri":"/manual/new-testament-student-study-guide/the-revelation-of-saint-john-the-divine/revelation-2-3-counsel-for-seven-branches-of-the-church.f5"},["img",{"src":"http://www.lds.org/bc/content/shared/content/images/gospel-library/manual/34188/p-165-1.gif"}]],[".intro",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/nt/rev/2"},"Revelation 2–3"],"contains counsel that John gave to seven branches of the Church in his day. You will notice, however, that John was simply the messenger; the words are the counsel of the Lord. Like the counsel given to us today through our leaders, the purpose of the counsel in",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/nt/rev/2"},"Revelation 2–3"],"was to encourage members to live according to Christ’s teachings and receive the blessings of the gospel. It should not be too difficult to understand how the counsel given in these chapters applies to Church members in our day. You will especially want to note the promises the Lord gave to the faithful. They are still true today."]],[".bodyBlock",[".topic",["h2","Understanding the Scriptures"],[".figure",{"id":"f6","uri":"/manual/new-testament-student-study-guide/the-revelation-of-saint-john-the-divine/revelation-2-3-counsel-for-seven-branches-of-the-church.f6"},["p"],["h2",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/nt/rev/2"},"Revelation 2"]],["p"],["table",["tbody",["tr",["td",["b","Bear"],"(v. 2)"],["td","Put up with, endure"],["td"]],["tr",["td",["b","Tried"],"(vv. 2, 10)"],["td","Tested (to see if they were true)"],["td"]],["tr",["td",["b","Borne"],"(v. 3)"],["td","Endured"],["td"]],["tr",["td",["b","Nicolaitans"],"(vv. 6, 15)"],["td","A group of people who believed in certain false teachings and who allowed—even encouraged—immoral actions, but who apparently acted secretly"],["td"]],["tr",["td",["b","Tribulation"],"(vv. 9–10, 22)"],["td","Trials and suffering"],["td"]],["tr",["td",["b","Blasphemy"],"(v. 9)"],["td","To speak lies or irreverently about sacred things"],["td"]],["tr",["td",["b","The second death"],"(v. 11)"],["td","To be shut out of the presence of the Lord forever"],["td"]],["tr",["td",["b","Thou holdest fast"],"(vv. 13, 25)"],["td","You stay faithful"],["td"]],["tr",["td",["b","Martyr"],"(v. 13)"],["td","A person who is killed for his or her beliefs"],["td"]],["tr",["td",["b","Seduce"],"(v. 20)"],["td","Lead away, tempt"],["td"]],["tr",["td",["b","Vessels of a potter"],"(v. 27)"],["td","Clay pots"],["td"]],["tr",["td",["b","Shivers"],"(v. 27)"],["td","Pieces"],["td"]],["tr",["td",["b","The morning star"],"(v. 28)"],["td","Refers to Jesus Christ (see",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/nt/rev/22.16"},"Revelation 22:16"],")"],["td"]]]]],[".topic",["h3",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/nt/rev/2"},"Revelation 2"],"—Important Changes from the Joseph Smith Translation"],["p.para",{"id":"p51","uri":"/manual/new-testament-student-study-guide/the-revelation-of-saint-john-the-divine/revelation-2-3-counsel-for-seven-branches-of-the-church.p51"},"The Joseph Smith Translation for",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/nt/rev/2.1,8,12"},"Revelation 2:1, 8, 12"],", and 18 changes the word",["span.emphasis","angel"],"to",["span.emphasis","servant."],"(It is also changed for",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/nt/rev/3"},"Revelation 3"],".) In",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/nt/rev/2.22"},"Revelation 2:22"],"the Joseph Smith Translation changes the word",["span.emphasis","bed"],"to",["span.emphasis","hell."],"It also changes",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/nt/rev/2.26-27"},"Revelation 2:26–27"],", making it clear that the “rod of iron” by which Jesus rules is the word of God (see",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/bofm/1-ne/15.23-24"},"1 Nephi 15:23–24"],") and that He rules with truth, justice, and equity—not with the seeming harshness verse 27 conveys."]],[".topic",["h3",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/nt/rev/2.2,9,13,19"},"Revelation 2:2, 9, 13, 19"],"(see also",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/nt/rev/3.1,8,15"},"Revelation 3:1, 8, 15"],")—“I Know Thy Works”"],["p.para",{"id":"p52","uri":"/manual/new-testament-student-study-guide/the-revelation-of-saint-john-the-divine/revelation-2-3-counsel-for-seven-branches-of-the-church.p52"},"The Lord made it clear to each of the branches that He sees and knows all their doings. He could say the same to us. He knows all of our thoughts, words, and actions."]],[".topic",["h3",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/nt/rev/2.7,11,17,26"},"Revelation 2:7, 11, 17, 26"],"(see also",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/nt/rev/3.5,12,21"},"Revelation 3:5, 12, 21"],")—“To Him That Overcometh” or “He That Overcometh”"],["p.para",{"id":"p53","uri":"/manual/new-testament-student-study-guide/the-revelation-of-saint-john-the-divine/revelation-2-3-counsel-for-seven-branches-of-the-church.p53"},"The Lord’s promises to the branches of the Church are worded differently, but they all refer to eternal life and exaltation in the celestial kingdom. It is helpful and interesting to read the different ways exaltation is described in",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/nt/rev/2"},"Revelation 2–3"],"."],["ul.bullet",["li",["span.label","•"],["p.para","The “tree of life” (",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/nt/rev/2.7"},"Revelation 2:7"],") refers to eternal life (see",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/nt/rev/22.2"},"Revelation 22:2"],")."]],["li",["span.label","•"],["p.para","The “crown of life” (",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/nt/rev/2.10"},"Revelation 2:10"],") and the promise of ruling (see",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/nt/rev/2.27"},"Revelation 2:27"],") refer to the blessing in the celestial kingdom of ruling as kings and priests forever (see",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/dc-testament/dc/76.56"},"D&C 76:56"],")."]],["li",["span.label","•"],["p.para","The white stone with a new name on it (see",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/nt/rev/2.17"},"Revelation 2:17"],") is only given to those who obtain the celestial kingdom (see",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/dc-testament/dc/130.10-11"},"D&C 130:10–11"],")."]],["li",["span.label","•"],["p.para","Those who are clothed in white and whose names are written in the book of life (see",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/nt/rev/3.4-5"},"Revelation 3:4–5"],") are those who are sanctified and inherit the celestial kingdom (see",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/dc-testament/dc/88.2"},"D&C 88:2"],")."]],["li",["span.label","•"],["p.para","Those who have the name of God written on them (see",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/nt/rev/3.12"},"Revelation 3:12"],") are gods themselves, which is the promised blessing of those who are exalted (see",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/dc-testament/dc/76.58"},"D&C 76:58"],")."]],["li",["span.label","•"],["p.para","To sit with Christ on His throne (see",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/nt/rev/3.21"},"Revelation 3:21"],") is to be as He is. This blessing is only given to those who inherit exaltation in the highest degree of the celestial kingdom (see",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/dc-testament/dc/132.20"},"D&C 132:20"],")."]]],["p.para",{"id":"p60","uri":"/manual/new-testament-student-study-guide/the-revelation-of-saint-john-the-divine/revelation-2-3-counsel-for-seven-branches-of-the-church.p60"},"It is significant that these promises of exaltation were given after the Lord explained ways the people had sinned. The Lord is merciful, and those who have sinned can obtain eternal life if they will repent."],[".figure",{"id":"f8","uri":"/manual/new-testament-student-study-guide/the-revelation-of-saint-john-the-divine/revelation-2-3-counsel-for-seven-branches-of-the-church.f8"},["p"],["h3",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/nt/rev/3"},"Revelation 3"]],["p"],["table",["tbody",["tr",["td",["b","Thou holdest fast"],"(vv. 3, 11)"],["td","You stay faithful"],["td"]],["tr",["td",["b","Defiled"],"(v. 4)"],["td","Made unclean (spiritually unclean through sin)"],["td"]],["tr",["td",["b","Key of David"],"(v. 7)"],["td","The power to rule"],["td"]],["tr",["td",["b","The Amen"],"(v. 14)"],["td","A term, referring to Christ, that means “the true one”"],["td"]],["tr",["td",["b","Wretched"],"(v. 17)"],["td","Enduring troubles, afflicted"],["td"]],["tr",["td",["b","Eyesalve"],"(v. 18)"],["td","Eye medicine"],["td"]],["tr",["td",["b","Rebuke and chasten"],"(v. 19)"],["td","Correct and discipline"],["td"]],["tr",["td",["b","Zealous"],"(v. 19)"],["td","Sincere and diligent"],["td"]]]]]],[".topic",["h3",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/nt/rev/3.1"},"Revelation 3:1"],"—“Thou Livest, and Art Dead”"],["p.para",{"id":"p69","uri":"/manual/new-testament-student-study-guide/the-revelation-of-saint-john-the-divine/revelation-2-3-counsel-for-seven-branches-of-the-church.p69"},"Elder Spencer W. Kimball, then a member of the Quorum of the Twelve Apostles, taught: “There are many people in this Church today who think they live, but they are dead to the spiritual things. … Their service is much of the letter and less of the spirit” (in Conference Report, Apr. 1951, 105)."]],[".topic",["h3",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/nt/rev/3.20"},"Revelation 3:20"],"—“I Stand at the Door, and Knock”"],["p.para",{"id":"p70","uri":"/manual/new-testament-student-study-guide/the-revelation-of-saint-john-the-divine/revelation-2-3-counsel-for-seven-branches-of-the-church.p70"},"Elder Spencer W. Kimball, then a member of the Quorum of the Twelve Apostles, told the following story about",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/nt/rev/3.20"},"Revelation 3:20"],":"],["p.para",{"id":"p71","uri":"/manual/new-testament-student-study-guide/the-revelation-of-saint-john-the-divine/revelation-2-3-counsel-for-seven-branches-of-the-church.p71"},"“Holman Hunt, the artist, felt inspired to capture this stirring scripture on canvas. One day he was showing his picture of ‘Christ Knocking at the Door’ to a friend when the friend suddenly exclaimed: ‘There is one thing wrong about your picture.’"],["p.para",{"id":"p72","uri":"/manual/new-testament-student-study-guide/the-revelation-of-saint-john-the-divine/revelation-2-3-counsel-for-seven-branches-of-the-church.p72"},"“‘What is it?’ inquired the artist."],["p.para",{"id":"p73","uri":"/manual/new-testament-student-study-guide/the-revelation-of-saint-john-the-divine/revelation-2-3-counsel-for-seven-branches-of-the-church.p73"},"“‘The door on which Jesus knocks has no handle,’ replied his friend."],["p.para",{"id":"p74","uri":"/manual/new-testament-student-study-guide/the-revelation-of-saint-john-the-divine/revelation-2-3-counsel-for-seven-branches-of-the-church.p74"},"“‘Ah,’ responded Mr. Hunt, ‘that is not a mistake. You see, this is the door to the human heart. It can only be opened from the inside.’"],["p.para",{"id":"p75","uri":"/manual/new-testament-student-study-guide/the-revelation-of-saint-john-the-divine/revelation-2-3-counsel-for-seven-branches-of-the-church.p75"},"“And thus it is. Jesus may stand and knock, but each of us decides whether to open. The Spirit is powerless to compel a man to move. The man himself must take the initiative” (",["span.emphasis","The Miracle of Forgiveness"],"[1969], 212)."]]],[".topic",["h2","Studying the Scriptures"],["p.para",{"id":"p76","uri":"/manual/new-testament-student-study-guide/the-revelation-of-saint-john-the-divine/revelation-2-3-counsel-for-seven-branches-of-the-church.p76"},"Do the following two activities (A and B) as you study",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/nt/rev/2"},"Revelation 2–3"],"."],[".topic",["h3",["img",{"src":"http://www.lds.org/bc/content/shared/content/images/gospel-library/manual/34188/icon-a.gif"}],"Organize What You Read"],["p.para",{"id":"p77","uri":"/manual/new-testament-student-study-guide/the-revelation-of-saint-john-the-divine/revelation-2-3-counsel-for-seven-branches-of-the-church.p77"},"The Lord’s counsel to each of the seven branches of the Church in Asia follows a pattern: He repeated one of the descriptions of Himself from",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/nt/rev/1"},"Revelation 1"],", He told the members of the branch what they were doing that pleased Him, He told them in what ways they needed to repent, and He told them of the blessings that would come if they were faithful. Make a chart in your notebook like the one below, and fill it in with information you find in",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/nt/rev/2"},"Revelation 2–3"],"."],[".figure",{"id":"f9","uri":"/manual/new-testament-student-study-guide/the-revelation-of-saint-john-the-divine/revelation-2-3-counsel-for-seven-branches-of-the-church.f9"},["table",["tbody",["tr",["th",["p.para",["b","City"]]],["th",["p.para",["b","Description of Christ"]]],["th",["p.para",["b","What they were doing that pleased the Lord"]]],["th",["p.para",["b","What they needed to repent of"]]],["th",["p.para",["b","Promised blessings"]]]],["tr",["td",["p.para","Ephesus (see",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/nt/rev/2.1-7"},"Revelation 2:1–7"],")"]],["td",["p.para"]],["td",["p.para"]],["td",["p.para"]],["td",["p.para"]]],["tr",["td",["p.para","Smyrna (see",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/nt/rev/2.8-11"},"Revelation 2:8–11"],")"]],["td",["p.para"]],["td",["p.para"]],["td",["p.para"]],["td",["p.para"]]],["tr",["td",["p.para","Pergamos (see",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/nt/rev/2.12-17"},"Revelation 2:12–17"],")"]],["td",["p.para"]],["td",["p.para"]],["td",["p.para"]],["td",["p.para"]]],["tr",["td",["p.para","Thyatira (see",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/nt/rev/2.18-29"},"Revelation 2:18–29"],")"]],["td",["p.para"]],["td",["p.para"]],["td",["p.para"]],["td",["p.para"]]],["tr",["td",["p.para","Sardis (see",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/nt/rev/3.1-6"},"Revelation 3:1–6"],")"]],["td",["p.para"]],["td",["p.para"]],["td",["p.para"]],["td",["p.para"]]],["tr",["td",["p.para","Philadelphia (see",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/nt/rev/3.7-13"},"Revelation 3:7–13"],")"]],["td",["p.para"]],["td",["p.para"]],["td",["p.para"]],["td",["p.para"]]],["tr",["td",["p.para","Laodicea (see",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/nt/rev/3.14-22"},"Revelation 3:14–22"],")"]],["td",["p.para"]],["td",["p.para"]],["td",["p.para"]],["td",["p.para"]]]]]]],[".topic",["h3",["img",{"src":"http://www.lds.org/bc/content/shared/content/images/gospel-library/manual/34188/icon-b.gif"}],"Applying the Scriptures to Your Life"],[".figure",{"id":"f10","uri":"/manual/new-testament-student-study-guide/the-revelation-of-saint-john-the-divine/revelation-2-3-counsel-for-seven-branches-of-the-church.f10"},["ol.number",["li",["span.label","1."],["p.para","What counsel given to the seven branches of the Church in Asia do you think most applies to the Church today? Why?"]],["li",["span.label","2."],["p.para","Which of the promises the Lord gave to the seven Churches (see “Understanding the Scriptures” for",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/nt/rev/2"},"Revelation 2"],") most inspires you to seek eternal life? Why?"]]]]]]],[".resources"]]]],"refs":null}
